<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Frankenia</i> <i>salina</i> is dominant or co-dominant in the herbaceous and subshrub layers with <i>Agrostis</i> <i>avenacea</i>, <i>Arthrocnemum</i> <i>subterminale</i>, <i>Atriplex</i> spp., <i>Batis</i> <i>maritima</i>, <i>Cressa</i> <i>truxillensis</i>, <i>Distichlis</i> <i>spicata</i>, <i>Hordeum</i> <i>murinum</i>, <i>Lasthenia</i> spp., <i>Lepidium</i> spp., <i>Limonium</i> <i>californicum</i>, <i>Monanthochloe</i> <i>littoralis</i>, <i>Sarcocornia</i> <i>pacifica</i> and <i>Suaeda</i> <i>taxifolia</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs and subshrubs < 60 cm; cover is open to continuous. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Frankenia salina</i> > 30% relative cover in the herbaceous layer, sometimes co-dominant with <i>Distichlis spicata</i> or other herbs and subshrubs (Keeler-Wolf and Vaghti 2000).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Coastal salt marshes, brackish marshes, alkali meadows, alkali playas. Soils are saline, sandy to clayey alluvium. The USFWS Wetland Inventory (1996 national list) recognizes <i>Frankenia salina</i> as a FACW+ plant. </div>
</div>

        
